I , on whom my Hopes depend , Do not this Work to Servants Care commend : If Thou thyself with me refuse to go , Here , to the listening Vines , I'll vent my Woe ; Still prostrate lie , lamenting for my Son , Till every Hill prove vocal to my Moan
